                           of the quires, one pair close to the head and one pair close to the tail
                           of the codex.&#xD; Chains of endband stitches are visible in the upper
                           part of the spine cover.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b5">Blind tooled ornament on the reddish-brown leather
                           cover (at least 6 tools were used: triple line fillet, double circle,
                           corni-form, small x, double sine wave with dots, criss cross).</decoNote>
